{"id":110066,"date":"2022-05-19T15:22:19","date_gmt":"2022-05-19T05:22:19","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/?p=110066"},"modified":"2022-05-19T15:22:19","modified_gmt":"2022-05-19T05:22:19","slug":"sbo-pathway-visa-491","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/sbo-pathway-visa-491\/","title":{"rendered":"Small Business Owner pathway"},"content":{"rendered":"[vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#8221; overflow=&#8221;visible&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; shape_divider_position=&#8221;bottom&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221;][vc_column column_padding=&#8221;no-extra-padding&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; column_position=&#8221;default&#8221; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/1&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; tablet_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; phone_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; animation_type=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221;][vc_column_text]Australia&#8217;s General Skilled Migration Program (<strong>Skill Stream<\/strong>, also referred to as the Points Tested Skilled Migration Program) is constantly evolving and changes to the way in which the program operates are designed to support economic development in Australia, meet Australia&#8217;s labour market needs and enhance future competitiveness and prosperity.<\/p>\n<p>Applications for some Skilled visas can only be lodged through <strong>SkillSelect<\/strong>, for example:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/skilled-independent-189-visa\/\">Skilled Independent visa (Subclass 189)<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/skilled-nominated-190-visa\/\">Skilled Nominated Visa (Subclass 190)<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/skilled-work-regional-491-visa\/\">Skilled Work Regional (Provisional) visa (Subclass 491) Visa<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>The Department of Home Affairs allows the different States and Territories to nominate applicants for <strong>Subclass 190<\/strong> and <strong>Subclass 491<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>Before the State\/Territory Nomination process can commence, applicants must meet the Department\u2019s criteria including:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>be under the age of 45 at the time of invitation<\/li>\n<li>have a nominated occupation on the relevant list of eligible skilled occupations<\/li>\n<li>have a valid and positive skills assessment for your nominated occupation<\/li>\n<li>have at least 65 points on the Department of Home Affairs points test<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n[\/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; top_padding=&#8221;10&#8243; constrain_group_1=&#8221;yes&#8221; bottom_padding=&#8221;10&#8243; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_position=&#8221;default&#8221; row_position_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; row_position_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; overflow=&#8221;visible&#8221; pointer_events=&#8221;all&#8221;][vc_column_inner column_padding=&#8221;padding-2-percent&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;small_depth&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;3px&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; advanced_gradient_angle=&#8221;0&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/1&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; animation_type=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221; gradient_type=&#8221;default&#8221;]<div class=\"iwithtext\"><div class=\"iwt-icon\"> <i class=\"icon-default-style fa fa-info extra-color-1\"><\/i> <\/div><div class=\"iwt-text\"> Each State and Territory set out their own nomination criteria depending on their labour market needs. Some States also have dedicated program streams for candidates who wish to use their business and entrepreneur skills to apply for State sponsorship.<\/p>\n<p>This is known as the\u00a0<strong>Small Business Owner (SBO)<\/strong>\u00a0pathway. <\/div><div class=\"clear\"><\/div><\/div>[\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_position=&#8221;default&#8221; row_position_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; row_position_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; overflow=&#8221;visible&#8221; pointer_events=&#8221;all&#8221;][vc_column_inner column_padding=&#8221;no-extra-padding&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/1&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; animation_type=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221;][vc_column_text]\n<h2>SBO Pathway<\/h2>\n<p>There are currently three States offering SBO pathways: <strong>Queensland<\/strong>, <strong>Tasmania<\/strong> and <strong>Canberra<\/strong>.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#8221; overflow=&#8221;visible&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; shape_divider_position=&#8221;bottom&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221;][vc_column column_padding=&#8221;padding-5-percent&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color=&#8221;#f7f7f7&#8243; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;3px&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; column_position=&#8221;default&#8221; advanced_gradient_angle=&#8221;0&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/1&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; tablet_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; phone_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; animation_type=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; gradient_type=&#8221;default&#8221;][vc_column_text]\n<h2><strong>Queensland<\/strong><\/h2>\n<p>Queensland offers an SBO pathway under the Visa Subclass 491. Some of the key requirements include:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>applicants must have full-time work rights and must not be currently studying\u200b.<\/li>\n<li>applicants must purchase an existing business in regional Queensland, for a minimum of $100,000\u200b.<\/li>\n<li>the business purchased must have existed for a minimum of 2 years prior to purchase.<\/li>\n<li>applicants must operate the business for a minimum of 6 months after settlement (100% paid)\u200b.<\/li>\n<li>applicants must employ at least 1 person that is not a family member and is either a permanent resident, Australian or New Zealand citizen (444) visa.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Applicants who have started their own business<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>must have operated the business for a minimum of 2 years before applying\u200b.<\/li>\n<li>must be generating a profit.<\/li>\n<li>must have a minimum turnover of $200,000.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n[\/vc_column_text][nectar_btn size=&#8221;small&#8221; open_new_tab=&#8221;true&#8221; button_style=&#8221;see-through&#8221; button_color_2=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; icon_family=&#8221;none&#8221; text=&#8221;Learn more&#8221; url=&#8221;https:\/\/migration.qld.gov.au\/visa-options\/skilled-visas\/small-business-owners-operating-in-regional&#8221;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#8221; overflow=&#8221;visible&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; shape_divider_position=&#8221;bottom&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221;][vc_column column_padding=&#8221;padding-5-percent&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color=&#8221;#f7f7f7&#8243; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;3px&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; column_position=&#8221;default&#8221; advanced_gradient_angle=&#8221;0&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/1&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; tablet_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; phone_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; animation_type=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; gradient_type=&#8221;default&#8221;][vc_column_text]\n<h2><strong>Tasmania<\/strong><\/h2>\n<p>Tasmania offers an SBO pathway under the Visa Subclass 491. Some of the key requirements include:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>applicants must operate the business for a minimum of 6 months (solely owned).<\/li>\n<li>the business must be able to generate a personal income that would meet the minimum taxable income requirement for the subclass 191 Permanent Residence (Skilled Regional) visa (AU$53,900 per year for at least 3 years in the next 5 years).<\/li>\n<li>applicants must show their understanding of the responsibilities and requirements around treating employees fairly by completing key units on the Fair Work Ombudsman\u2019s online learning centre (see the Document Checklist &#8211; Category 5 Small Business Owner information).<\/li>\n<li>applicants must provide a comprehensive business plan.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n[\/vc_column_text][nectar_btn size=&#8221;small&#8221; open_new_tab=&#8221;true&#8221; button_style=&#8221;see-through&#8221; button_color_2=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; icon_family=&#8221;none&#8221; text=&#8221;Learn more&#8221; url=&#8221;https:\/\/www.migration.tas.gov.au\/skilled_migrants\/skilled_regional&#8221;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#8221; overflow=&#8221;visible&#8221; advanced_gradient_angle=&#8221;0&#8243; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; shape_divider_position=&#8221;bottom&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; gradient_type=&#8221;default&#8221; shape_type=&#8221;&#8221;][vc_column column_padding=&#8221;padding-5-percent&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color=&#8221;#f7f7f7&#8243; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;3px&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; column_position=&#8221;default&#8221; advanced_gradient_angle=&#8221;0&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/1&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; tablet_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; phone_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; animation_type=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; gradient_type=&#8221;default&#8221;][vc_column_text]\n<h2><strong>Canberra<\/strong><\/h2>\n<p>The Australian Capital Territory (ACT) offers an SBO pathway under the Visa Subclass 190 AND Visa Subclass 491. Some of the key requirements include:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>the applicant must be the majority owner of an eligible registered business located in the ACT and must be claiming Matrix points in the Small Business Owner category.<\/li>\n<li>the applicant\u2019s nominated occupation does not have to be on the ACT Critical Skills List.<\/li>\n<li>ACT 491 nomination: applicants must be working in Canberra for at least three months.<\/li>\n<li>ACT 190 nomination: applicants must be working in Canberra for at least six months.<\/li>\n<li>applicants MUST sign a statutory declaration confirming the details of their ACT Small Business activity.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n[\/vc_column_text][nectar_btn size=&#8221;small&#8221; open_new_tab=&#8221;true&#8221; button_style=&#8221;see-through&#8221; button_color_2=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; icon_family=&#8221;none&#8221; text=&#8221;Learn more&#8221; url=&#8221;https:\/\/www.act.gov.au\/migration\/skilled-migrants\/act-government-process\/act-nomination-process&#8221;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; top_padding=&#8221;20&#8243; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#82